The paper focuses on the application of attention mechanisms in the Visual Question Answering (VQA) task, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed method involves generating human-like attention maps, which requires machine learning techniques such as deep learning (cs.AI) and possibly reinforcement learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves evaluating the performance of the attention-based VQA model, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR).
